      <item>
        <title>Automatic Platform Optimization Cloudflare</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[juanma]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Hi <a class="mention" href="https://community.frontity.org/u/kent">@Kent</a>,</p>
<p>This is actually great news! With this service, HTML generated by WordPress can be also cached by this layer improving a lot the response time.</p>
<p>This service is similar to what other companies are already providing like <a href="https://www.strattic.com/">Strattic</a> &amp; <a href="https://www.getshifter.io/">Shifter</a></p>
<p>This reinforces the idea we have that the performance of a site doesn’t really have to do with the platform chosen to create the site (Wordpress vs Gatsby vs Frontity, for example) but with a good cache strategy</p>
<p></p><div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/original/2X/a/a4b2c79c34e0f625df61385cc17d95a8a8dd5147.png" data-download-href="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/a4b2c79c34e0f625df61385cc17d95a8a8dd5147" title="Fly-Fest_2020_-Headless_WordPress(4)"><img src="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/optimized/2X/a/a4b2c79c34e0f625df61385cc17d95a8a8dd5147_2_690x388.png" alt="Fly-Fest_2020_-Headless_WordPress(4)" data-base62-sha1="nuZl0VWn2TtmpsRFVpOlQnp54lp" width="690" height="388" srcset="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/optimized/2X/a/a4b2c79c34e0f625df61385cc17d95a8a8dd5147_2_690x388.png, https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/original/2X/a/a4b2c79c34e0f625df61385cc17d95a8a8dd5147.png 1.5x, https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/original/2X/a/a4b2c79c34e0f625df61385cc17d95a8a8dd5147.png 2x" data-small-upload="https://community.frontity.org/uploads/default/optimized/2X/a/a4b2c79c34e0f625df61385cc17d95a8a8dd5147_2_10x10.png"></a></div><p></p>
<p>And this Cloudflare’s APO will work perfectly fine with the new Embedded Mode feature we have in our roadmap</p>
<aside class="quote" data-post="26" data-topic="1432">
  <div class="title">
    <div class="quote-controls"></div>
    <img alt="" width="20" height="20" src="/user_avatar/community.frontity.org/luisherranz/40/735_2.png" class="avatar">
    <a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/embedded-mode/1432/26">Embedded mode</a> <a class="badge-wrapper  box" href="https://community.frontity.org/c/feature-discussions/needs-research/35"><span class="badge-category-parent-bg" style="background-color: #652D90;"></span><span class="badge-category-bg" style="background-color: #d3abff;"></span><span style="color: #FFFFFF" data-drop-close="true" class="badge-category clear-badge" title="Needs a research about the possible implementation before development.">Needs Research</span></a>
  </div>
  <blockquote>
    I have moved the proof of conecpt repository to the Frontity organization in GitHub and I have: 

Renamed it to Frontity Embedded.
Added a proper Readme for people that want to test it out.
Added support for environment variables.
Added a bypass for previews, that fall back to the PHP theme.

The new URL is:
  </blockquote>
</aside>

<p>With a good cache layer and Frontity you not only gain speed in your site but a better Developer Experience by creating your sites w/ React</p>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/automatic-platform-optimization-cloudflare/3070/3">Read full topic</a></p>
